From: byron@cc.gatech.edu (Byron A Jeff)
Subject: Re: ASCII to PostScript converter
Date: Thu, 19 Aug 1993 19:57:46 GMT

In article <CC0rEG.JqK@ra.nrl.navy.mil>,
Ankush Gosain <gosain@hci0.NoSubdomain.NoDomain> wrote:
>There is a utility called mpage which will do 2,4,8 pages of stuff to a printed page.  It
>even works on postscript files.  It is available from ftp.uu.net as
>/systems/ibmpc/msdos/simtel20/printer/mpage113.zip
                ^^^^^ - isn't this a linux newsgroup?

Try nenscript. Same functionality as enscript for the Suns with sources.
For compressing multipages try psnup.

Check you nearby archie server for both these.

